headline: Is Home Depot Stock Still Attractive After Recent Share Price Weakness?
summary: If you have ever wondered whether Home Depot at around $360 a share is a bargain or a trap, you are exactly the kind of investor this breakdown is for. Despite being down about 7.4% year to date and 11.6% over the last year, the stock is still up roughly 20.0% over three years and 50.2% over five, which tells a very different story if you zoom out. Recent moves in Home Depot stock have been shaped by ongoing debates about the strength of US consumer spending and the slowdown in big ticket...
